# Every text file checks out with LF bytes on every platform. The repository
# contains no intentionally-CRLF files (verified: zero CRLF blobs, no
# .bat/.cmd/.ps1), while three surfaces byte-compare checked-out files against
# LF-writing generators or content-derived hashes: contract surfaces
# (scripts/generate-all.mjs --check and the staged subgenerator tests, run on
# Windows in release.yml), copy-through generator INPUTS (crates/napi/types/),
# and test fixtures (clone fingerprints, snapshot assertions). Enumerating
# those surfaces missed inputs twice (v3.4.0 failed on the committed side
# being CRLF, v3.4.1 on a generator input being CRLF); the repo-wide default
# closes the class. Binary files are auto-detected and unaffected.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Kept for emphasis: fixture bytes feed content-derived hashes.
tests/fixtures/** text eol=lf
